1
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:13,080
Today, I want to find one person to join me at the booth.

2
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,920
Tid-Gift, you come with me today.

3
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:15,640
Huh?

4
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:18,400
Even Glamorous Airline is here at the booth?

5
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,400
Or is it because their sales are dropping?

6
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:24,120
Oh!

7
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:25,240
Are you okay?

8
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,600
Book your trip now and you’ll get a stylish, trendy T-shirt.

9
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:28,400
Book now, book now.

10
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,320
Please, right this way.

11
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:31,840
Damn, such a smooth seller.
How are we supposed to compete with that?

12
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:35,600
Are you sure you want to come back and fight again?

13
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,000
I shouldn’t run away.

14
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,520
I’m ready to come back and hunt you down, Glam.

15
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:55,000
Are you sure you want to come back and fight again?

16
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,320
I've been thinking...

17
00:01:57,320 --> 00:02:00,160
I shouldn’t run away.

18
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:01,640
But you flew away for so long...

19
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,800
I was regrouping.

20
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:03,800
That took you quite some time.

21
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:11,720
I’m ready to come back and hunt you down, Glam.

22
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,200
Oh, dear.

23
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,640
Oh, my...

24
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,480
Are you alright?

25
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:25,760
I'm alright.

26
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:27,080
Alright, okay.

27
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:30,360
I was standing here, she bumped into me.

28
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:31,360
Are you alright?

29
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,360
I'm alright.

30
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,400
Excuse me, ma'am.

31
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,080
Yes?

32
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,800
I am a police officer.

33
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,360
We have received a report that

34
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:43,880
illegal items have been smuggled into the country.

35
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,720
So what?

36
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:48,400
May I search your bag?

37
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:50,920
Yes, you may.
There is nothing inside anyway. Please go ahead.

38
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,640
Please do not waste time, officer.

39
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:56,640
There will only be amulets, prayer books, and rosaries.

40
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:57,920
Why don't you...

41
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:05,080
Oh, Madam, which temple blessed this one?

42
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:08,080
Wait a second, this is not mine.

43
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:10,080
So how did it end up in your bag, Madam?

44
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:15,920
This is the “Spinning Pleasure Charm,” Madam.

45
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:19,880
Siri, put it down.
It is not ours. Put it down.

46
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:20,880
Why are you being so possessive?

47
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,360
It is not mine.

48
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,680
With evidence this clear, we must also check your residence.

49
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,280
But I already told you that I know nothing about this.

50
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,880
If you go to my place, there will be nothing.

51
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:31,840
This bag is not my bag.

52
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,200
Please cooperate.

53
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:37,200
If you refuse to cooperate,
it means you are obstructing the officer’s duty.

54
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:48,920
Thank you so much.

55
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,960
Hey, what? This is not yours.

56
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:56,000
This is mine.
Tonight, I have a soccer match to watch.

57
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,000
What?

58
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,320
So are you still in touch with Madam Porn?

59
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,720
Hmm, not at all.

60
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,720
I noticed she went quiet.

61
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,800
Why do you ask?

62
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:12,880
Nothing.

63
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:16,200
So will you keep working here?

64
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,320
My family is in debt. What about you?

65
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:27,520
I will probably keep working.
I want to study how Glamorous Airline flies...

66
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:28,520
and avoids birds.

67
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,920
For what?

68
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:36,840
Well, I dream that I want to start my own airline.

69
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:39,360
Oh, okay, okay.

70
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
A meeting again, Chai?
I am about to eat.

71
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:50,320
So why don’t you bring sticky rice like these two?

72
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:55,000
Alright, Chai, just say what you want.

73
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,040
What meeting is this?

74
00:04:56,040 --> 00:05:00,040
Today, I want to find one person to join me at the booth.

75
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:04,720
I have a flight with Kreetha, Sky, and Chaba.

76
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:06,960
Only Tid-Gift is left, then.

77
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:12,000
Then, Tid-Gift, you come with me today.

78
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Meeting adjourned.

79
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:13,960
That’s all?

80
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,480
What?

81
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:18,480
Yes, that’s all.

82
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:25,480
Chai, next time if it’s just this,
you can just text in the group.

83
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:29,080
That’s true. You are the one
who makes the flight schedule anyway.

84
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:30,080
Why would you call us in for a meeting?

85
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,600
I just want to see everyone.

86
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,600
It looks like you are very lonely, Chai.

87
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:45,440
You will not find anything.
It is just a waste of time.

88
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:55,080
Please drink some cold water first, officer.

89
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,080
Thank you.

90
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,320
Is this really the time to serve, Siri?

91
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,560
They came here to search for evidence to arrest us.

92
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,560
Well, it is my duty.

93
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:05,920
Madam, if you are not guilty,
you do not need to be afraid.

94
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,240
I have found the evidence.

95
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:12,840
Here it is.

96
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:17,320
Why is there money transferred from the temple into this company?

97
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:20,320
Hey, no, this is wrong.
This is not mine.

98
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:41,040
How can it not be yours?
The name of your company is clearly stated here.

99
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:46,360
Porn Prang Pru Open Five Orifices to Receive Unlimited Wealth Company Limited.

100
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:50,880
A disgraceful company name like this exists only here, Madam.

101
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:51,800
A monk named it.

102
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,800
Sadhu.

103
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:57,400
Wait a second, me?
Embezzling temple money?

104
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,160
I only donate money to temples.

105
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:02,720
That is true.
Madam donates millions to temples.

106
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,760
She never takes even a single baht from them.

107
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:05,760
Sadhu.

108
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,160
Is that so?

109
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,240
Here, a monastic donation box.

110
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,240
Hey!

111
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,000
How did that get here?

112
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:28,760
Wait, this is not mine.

113
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,920
Someone must be framing me.

114
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:34,080
Then, bring evidence to prove you did not do it.

115
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:39,560
I will go check the CCTV footage from the office first, Madam.

116
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,560
Hmm.

117
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:01,240
Oh, my!

118
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:08,240
Oh, my...even Glamorous Airline is here at the booth?

119
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:12,280
I heard the airline’s booking numbers were booming, right?

120
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:15,760
So why are they still running promotions?

121
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:19,440
Or is it because their sales are dropping?

122
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:28,200
The numbers are not dropping.
But what is dropping is my jaw at your outfits.

123
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:31,600
Look over there, the spirit shrine.
Go that way.

124
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,560
Go!

125
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,280
No!

126
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:39,560
This is the theme of Porn Airline.

127
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:43,560
We came with the theme
“Travel Thailand with peace of mind in every region with...

128
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:47,640
Porn Airline.”

129
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,080
Then, I'll make an offering.

130
00:08:51,520 --> 00:09:01,520
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambuddhassa.

131
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,280
Sadhu.

132
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:06,760
We're humans, not beckoning cats!

133
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,040
Why are you serving red soda like this?

134
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,920
If you are going to have an event, you need a concept.

135
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:15,120
You need an idea. You need a storyboard.

136
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,520
You need creativity.

137
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,320
I should just kick you.

138
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,040
Oh my!

139
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:19,840
Go!

140
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:22,840
And this is the best you can do, being creative?

141
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,720
Hello.

142
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,120
Welcome, welcome. Please.

143
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:39,760
Please, this way.

144
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:45,280
Hello, welcome to Porn Airline.

145
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:50,000
Right now, we have a promotion to Chiang Mai.

146
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,800
Wow, three days and two nights with a special program.

147
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,280
No one else can ever do this again.

148
00:09:56,280 --> 00:10:01,160
I can say it is shocking, dazzling, magnificent,
and so much fun in the North.

149
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:04,600
It is guaranteed, truly guaranteed, that the two of us are...

150
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:08,160
I am a Chiang Mai woman.

151
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:12,160
Oh, not quite yet, but I will be one soon.

152
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:17,200
Every day, men come to flirt, to flirt, to flirt.

153
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,560
I must tell you there are so many places to visit.

154
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:23,560
You can pick green tea on Doi Pui.

155
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:27,560
Or you can go to Mae Salong to collect tea roots.

156
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:33,160
Wow, or you can bathe an elephant and get splashed like this.

157
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,640
Or you can eat Northern Thai Sausage at the walking street.

158
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:39,000
Yes, or you can scuba dive in Chiang Mai city.

159
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,200
That’s right, the water is crystal clear.

160
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:45,600
Yes, or you can roll up Doi Suthep.

161
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,600
We have it all.

162
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:50,840
What do you think, Chai?

163
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,840
Then, let’s do this.

164
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:56,240
Glamorous Airline has a very special promotion.

165
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:59,760
We offer everyone seven days and six nights in Japan.

166
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:02,160
You will receive exclusive services.

167
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:06,040
You can walk under cherry blossoms with Kumamon.

168
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:09,120
You can climb up and down Mount Fuji.

169
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:11,720
You can sleep in the middle of Shibuya Crossing.

170
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:15,720
And most importantly, you can ride to visit Nobita’s house.

171
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:20,520
That’s not all. You can drink matcha on Tokyo Tower.

172
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:25,960
All of this promotion is only 9,999 baht.

173
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:30,680
Hey!

174
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,240
Huh?

175
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:31,960
Come here.

176
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,600
I want to go to Japan!

177
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,200
The price is so good.

178
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,200
You can't. They are our competitor.

179
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:43,480
So what should we do?

180
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,880
We must make ours even more fabulous.

181
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,040
No need to fight.

182
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,160
Everyone will get it.

183
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,760
We're selling fast!

184
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,760
We really are selling fast!

185
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,760
What’s wrong, Chaba?

186
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:17,240
I feel sorry for that little bread.

187
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,840
Why’s that?

188
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:22,840
I don’t dare microwave it.

189
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,320
I’m afraid that poor bread will get hot.

190
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:29,240
Huh? You pity the bread?

191
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:33,240
Hey, why say that?
The microwave gets super hot, so many degrees!

192
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:40,200
And the bread...this tiny piece...
how could it endure that? There's no way.

193
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:52,720
Hey, All-New, go comfort Chaba.
She won’t stop crying!

194
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,040
Why is she crying?

195
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:56,640
She said she feels sorry for the bread.

196
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,080
Why is that?

197
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,920
Because the bread has to go into the microwave.

198
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:02,320
And she feels sorry it has to endure the heat.

199
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,160
And so what?

200
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,440
You’re the science whiz.

201
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:08,440
Go tell her the facts...
why bread needs to go in the microwave.

202
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:12,760
A microwave uses electromagnetic waves,

203
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,600
which make the water molecules in bread vibrate,

204
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,520
to create heat.
You tell her that...

205
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:18,960
Whoa! I didn’t get a single thing you just said.

206
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:21,960
I flunked physics. I’m dumb.
You explain it to her.

207
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:28,320
Chaba, you need to understand...

208
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:31,320
the bread has to go in the microwave so it’ll get warm.

209
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:37,080
What nonsense are you babbling?
Why are you butting in? I don’t get it.

210
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:39,920
Kreetha told me you were crying.

211
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:42,000
Hey!

212
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,440
Who’s crying?

213
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,720
I’m a strong woman.

214
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,480
This little thing wouldn’t make me cry.

215
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,480
It’s just a petty issue.

216
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,040
What chaos! I’m trying to work here.

217
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:53,040
Oh my gosh, what’s going on here?

218
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:56,200
The noise is spilling outside, oh dear.

219
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,240
But you’re the loudest of them all!

220
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:00,480
Oh, oops. Sorry.

221
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,840
Kreetha here said Chaba was crying.

222
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:07,000
She was upset about the bread going in the microwave.

223
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,080
And?

224
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:12,160
So I came in to comfort her but she snapped at me instead.

225
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:15,520
Chaba, are you on your period?

226
00:14:15,520 --> 00:14:19,200
Well, the passenger keeps asking me to microwave bread nonstop!

227
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:23,280
I’ve microwaved it five times already.
It’s driving me nuts.

228
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:26,640
I pity the bread, sure, but I’m forced to microwave it.

229
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:27,640
Who could endure this?

230
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:31,400
It’s okay.
She's my friend. I’ll handle it.

231
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,640
Keep microwaving, the topping is ruined now!

232
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:36,640
And you're that angry?

233
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,320
Yeah, just seeing your face pisses me off already.

234
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,160
Why are you standing here, huh?

235
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:47,160
Here, squeeze this.

236
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:56,640
Feeling better?

237
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,240
Nope, not helping.

238
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,520
What the hell did you give me to play with?

239
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:02,520
Fine, take this Enter key and press it.

240
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,120
I can just press it?

241
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:06,120
Go ahead. It’ll fix your anger.

242
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:08,840
More! Press harder!

243
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,320
Harder!

244
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:13,360
You press it yourself then.
It’s useless.

245
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:15,360
When you’re this wild, only my secret move will work.

246
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:16,280
What move?

247
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,280
Open your mouth.

248
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:19,560
Chew.

249
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,200
Better now?

250
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,320
Here, take another bite.

251
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,640
Yeah, chew it.

252
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,600
You think I’m a horse?

253
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,720
Buffalo. You're a damn buffalo.

254
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:46,600
How’s it going, Siri?

255
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:50,160
All the CCTV footage has been deleted, Madam.

256
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,000
All of it?

257
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,800
Yes, Madam.

258
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,760
You can't say that you're being framed now, then.

259
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:57,760
I still won’t accept it.
I didn’t do this.

260
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:01,320
On the suspect’s computer...

